Open Peninsula - licence and notice

This repository hosts a residents' campaign page about two planning
applications on the Greenwich Peninsula. Different parts are covered
differently.

1. CODE (the HTML, CSS and JavaScript in index.html, and robots.txt)
   MIT Licence (full text below). You are welcome to reuse the page
   structure and styling, including for your own community or campaign.

2. ORIGINAL TEXT (the words written for this page)
   Copyright (c) 2026 Open Peninsula. You may freely read, share, link to
   and quote this page. To republish substantial portions, or to adapt the
   text for another campaign, please get in touch first.

3. IMAGES, VIDEO, RENDERS AND EMBEDDED CLIPS
   Not licensed for reuse. They belong to their respective owners (the
   applicants and developer, the named photographer, news outlets, and the
   social-media creators credited on the page) and are included here only
   for criticism, review and reporting on a matter of public interest (fair
   dealing under UK copyright law). If you reuse the code, remove them and
   supply your own.

4. FONT
   "BDO Grotesk" (in /fonts) is provided under its own foundry licence and
   is not relicensed here.

